        options: ["Propranolol 20 mg BID, titrate to target heart rate 55-60 bpm","Metoprolol 25 mg BID, titrate to target heart rate 60-70 bpm","Lisinopril 10 mg daily, titrate to target blood pressure <130/80","Furosemide 40 mg daily, titrate to target weight loss of 0.5 kg/day"],
        correct: 0,
        rationale: "Non-selective beta-blockers (propranolol or nadolol) are first-line for primary prophylaxis of variceal hemorrhage. They reduce portal pressure by blocking beta-1 (reducing cardiac output) and beta-2 receptors (allowing splanchnic vasoconstriction). Target resting heart rate is 55-60 bpm. Selective beta-blockers like metoprolol lack beta-2 blockade and are NOT effective for portal pressure reduction."
